The Police Command in Bauchi has confirmed the killing of four persons by unidentified gunmen at Gambar Sabon-Layi community in Tafawa Balewa Local Government Area of the state. The Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), SP Ahmad Wakil confirmed the incident in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Bauchi on Sunday. He said the gunmen attacked the community at midnight on Saturday and abducted one other person. He said the Commissioner of Police, Aminu Alhassan had ordered a discreet investigation to arrest the culprits.